<font color="#FF0000">PROHIBITION WAS A RULE!</font><br>
<tt>Tue Dec  2 10:30:42 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
First, I would like to thank Art, Bob, Paul and Marc for their diligent combined efforts to keep this site alive and intact.  I respect the idealism embodied in the establishment of rules, but like the rules of engagement in war...rules here are likely to become the first casualty.<br>
I suggest that one's posting here does not limit him or herself to a few rote rules of conduct, but instead, recommend that every poster operate with a keen sense of respect for themselves and others.  Tom Dier is one to emulate.  <br>
To call any Marine a Jarhead or Infantryman a Grunt may be construed as a sign of disrespect or may be a title of endearment!  Veterans of combat, by virtue of service and experience, have earned an inviolate brotherhood that allows each to practice dark humor and teasing upon one another. Humor is based upon someone's misfortune.  Certainly, veterans of dangerous training activities and combat are special students of misfortune and tragedy.<br>
Laughter at one's self and others is often a prefered emotional release than that of crying or cursing.  It is certainly a projection that allows the astute observer to see hidden pain. There is indeed, a form of ridicule that actually conveys acceptance, but it is a narrow wave band that only a few are priviledged to transmit on.<br>
Conversly, ridicule from those who have not experienced deprivation and sacrifice in the ultimate service to their country, is not well received and falls upon hypersensitive ears.  Ridicule from an egocentric person assails the senses of ones who value demonstrated team work and self sacrifice, given for the unselfish reason that others may survive. Mockery from one who ran is not construed as amusing by <br>
those met the challenge.  Ridicule that is intended to debase, depersonalize, invalidate or taunt victims of combat service in order to remove the troublesome focus upon one's own acts of treason or cowardice is a crime.<br>
There is only one person on this site, although he appears under different names, who is the problem.  An assessment of his performance may provide an instant list of &quot;causes for fire fights,&quot; the crude and vulgar statement he made about sexual predation on a 13 year old girl is a blatant example!<br>
It is difficult to propose a valid strategy that will immune this site to his antagonistic and self serving approach and vile, caustic, deportment.  One can not legislate flies away from a picnic.  Flies do not follow human rules!  We, then, are left with one realistic alternative...just brush him aside as we would a noisey, filthy fly...or stay home and miss the camraderie of an otherwise good picnic.<br>
Rules are laws...laws are not laws unless they are enforced! We are not allowed to enforce gag rules here because of the principles of freedom of speech...and public access, but we can in good judgement and language develop a verbal fly swatter!
